Step 1: Verify Architecture
uname -m
Expected:
arm64
Step 2: Download Prometheus
Download:
prometheus-3.12.0.darwin-arm64.tar.gz
Step 3: Extract Prometheus
cd ~/Downloads

tar -xzf prometheus-3.12.0.darwin-arm64.tar.gz

cd prometheus-3.12.0.darwin-arm64
Step 4: Remove macOS Quarantine
xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine .
Step 5: Verify Prometheus Binary
file ./prometheus
Expected:
Mach-O 64-bit executable arm64
Step 6: Start Prometheus
./prometheus --config.file=prometheus.yml
Expected:
Server is ready to receive web requests.
Step 7: Open Prometheus UI
Browser:
http://localhost:9090
Step 8: Verify Prometheus Works
PromQL:
up
Expected:
up{job="prometheus"} 1
Step 9: Download Node Exporter
Download:
node_exporter-1.9.x.darwin-arm64.tar.gz
(Use the latest available version.)
Step 10: Extract Node Exporter
cd ~/Downloads

tar -xzf node_exporter-*.darwin-arm64.tar.gz

cd node_exporter-*
Step 11: Verify Binary
file ./node_exporter
Expected:
Mach-O 64-bit executable arm64
Step 12: Remove macOS Quarantine
xattr -dr com.apple.quarantine .
Step 13: Start Node Exporter
Open a NEW terminal:
cd ~/Downloads/node_exporter-*
./node_exporter
Expected:
Listening on :9100
Step 14: Verify Metrics Endpoint
Open:
http://localhost:9100/metrics
You should see thousands of metrics.
Step 15: Update prometheus.yml
Open:
nano ~/Downloads/prometheus-3.12.0.darwin-arm64/prometheus.yml
Add Node Exporter:
global:
  scrape_interval: 15s

scrape_configs:

  - job_name: "prometheus"
    static_configs:
      - targets: ["localhost:9090"]

  - job_name: "node-exporter"
    static_configs:
      - targets: ["localhost:9100"]
Save:
CTRL + O
ENTER
CTRL + X
Step 16: Restart Prometheus
Stop:
CTRL + C
Start again:
./prometheus --config.file=prometheus.yml
Step 17: Verify Targets
Go to:
Status → Targets
Expected:
prometheus      UP
node-exporter   UP
Step 18: CPU Monitoring
PromQL:
100 - (avg by(instance) (rate(node_cpu_seconds_total{mode="idle"}[5m])) * 100)
Shows CPU utilization %.
Step 19: Memory Monitoring
(node_memory_MemTotal_bytes - node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes)
/
node_memory_MemTotal_bytes * 100
Shows memory utilization %.
Step 20: Disk Monitoring
100 -
(node_filesystem_avail_bytes * 100 /
node_filesystem_size_bytes)
Shows disk usage %.
Step 21: Network Monitoring
Incoming traffic:
rate(node_network_receive_bytes_total[5m])
Outgoing traffic:
rate(node_network_transmit_bytes_total[5m])
Step 22: System Load
node_load1
Step 23: System Uptime
node_time_seconds - node_boot_time_seconds
